deck: With their world turned upside down, Coulson races to save the life of his one true love as the mystery of “The Cellist” is finally revealed.
name: The Only Light in the Darkness

deck: Just when there's no one left to trust, Agent Maria Hill returns to team up with Coulson as S.H.I.E.L.D. is being destroyed around them.
description:
Just when there's no one left to trust, Agent Maria Hill (Cobie Smulders) - from "Marvel's The Avengers" and Marvel's "Captain America: The Winter Solider" - returns to team up with Coulson as S.H.I.E.L.D. is being destroyed around them.

"Nothing Personal" was written by Paul Zbyszewski & DJ Doyle and directed by Billy Gierhart.
name: Nothing Personal
The Many Faces of Gideon Flinch

deck: Size doesn't matter in this episode.
description:
In an attempt to steal back Reed Richards latest discovery, Psycho-Man comes knocking at the Baxter Building's front door. What is Reed's latest discovery you say? Well, it's a mysterious formula, which originated from Psycho-Man's turf, the absolutely microscopic, Microverse, and he asks the team to give it back, the hard way. This certain formula can alter a host's personality, from all good to all bad. Unfortunately, Susan Storm has been exposed to that little formula, which turned her to the vile Malice. Now attempting to destroy her friends, Reed, Ben and Johnny must travel to the Microverse to save Sue, especially themselves.

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation of Fantastic Four Issues #76, #77 and #280 until #283.
name: Worlds Within Worlds

deck: Earth is on a collision course with the living planet, Ego!
description:
Earth's experiencing a large string of events concerning the environment. Tornadoes are wrecking havok, fires are breaking out, and tsunamis are wiping the Earth clean. In a desperate act to save the world, the Fantastic Four travel to deep space to investigate, and what they discovered shocked them. They found Ego, the Living Planet, and this certain planet is out to destroy the world. Luckily, Thor is out to give a hand, but it ain't gonna save them. For their last stand, they're gonna need the assistance of the Devourer of Worlds himself, Galactus.

Note 1: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic Four Issues #234 and #235.

Note 2: Several characters in this episode, mainly the Avengers (Iron Man, Captain America, Goliath, She-Hulk, Vision and Hercules) and the New Warriors (Speedball, Rage, Justice and Darkhawk) only made physical cameos battling Ego.

Sub-Note 2.5: Hawkeye makes a cameo here under his Goliath identity.
name: To Battle the Living Planet

deck: The Fantastic Four meets the king of the jungle, Black Panther!
description:
After the cataclysmic battle between the heroes and Ego, the Living Planet, the Fantastic Four gets a new extension called, The Four Freedoms Plaza. As they settle in their new home, the young leader of the nation known as Wakanda, comes to the Fantastic Four, but he's not asking for help. His name is T'Challa, also known as the Black Panther, and he comes in the building in full force. But as the team battle against the king, they realize that he's just using them as practice for a much bigger prey. The hunter's real target is the master of sound, Klaw.

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic Four Issues #52 and #53
name: Prey of the Black Panther

description:
Poor Johnny Storm is still depress after his break-up with the Inhuman Crystal, but that depression soon goes away when he meets Frankie Raye, a superhuman with the same fire powers as his. Meanwhile, Terrax arrives at New York City and suddenly caused the entire island to rise in thin air. Terrax demands that the Fantastic Four defeat Galactus, and the team agrees. Later, they realized that Terrax betrayed Galactus and he lead him here so that Earth will be destroyed. Frankie's fate must be determined, whether she becomes Galctus's next herald so that Earth may be spared, or the world dies. Looks like Daniel Ketch and Thor's intervention may be useless here.

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic Four Issues #242 until #244.
name: When Calls Galactus

deck: The Incredible Hulk rages through Manhattan!
description:
Dr. Bruce Banner, better known as the Incredible Hulk, travels to New York City to visit the Fantastic Four in the hopes of ridding Hulk from his system, for good. Joining him is his sidekick and long time friend, Rick Jones. While Mr. Fantastic aids Bruce in his efforts to find a cure, the malevolent Doctor Doom returns with a vengeance. In order to destroy his enemies once and for all, he controls the green goliath to destroy the Fantastic Four. Can the team stop him before Hulk destroys New York, and them?

Note 1: This is one of two episodes of the second season that has an original script instead of an adaptation. The other being "Hopelessly Impossible".

Note 2: Several characters in this episode, mainly the X-Men (Cyclops, Wolverine, Storm, Jean Grey and Gambit), Ben Reilly and Juggernaut only made physical cameos as the people that were passed by Johnny Storm and Rick Jones in their Airject Cycle.
name: Nightmare in Green

deck: Susan Storm is dying, and there's only one man who can save her.
description:
Susan Storm is on the verge of death. There are no options left for the Fantastic Four, but one. Dr. Franklin Storm, Johnny and Susan Storm's father, is that option. Mr. Storm was charged for a murder case which is believed to be linked to him, and thus has disappeared from the public eye. The team was able to find him, and Mr. Storm operates on his daughter, which lead out to be a success. However, the sweet reunion between children and father has been cut short after authorities took him in. Elsewhere, the Skrulls are planning their revenge against the team, and they decided to impersonate Mr. Storm, then infiltrate them. Can the team fight the faker?

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic four Issues #32 and #37.
name: Behold, A Distant Star

deck: The Impossible Man breaks into the Four Freedoms Plaza.
description:
The Fantastic Four are currently out for a while, and their headquarters is nearly empty. Human Torch and his pal, Lockjaw seems to be the caretakers of their home. While the two guard the building, an unimaginable force enters the Four Freedoms Plaza. That force is non-other than the Impossible Man, an annoying shape-shifter from Poppup. Eager to visit the team, he finds the building completely silent. Impossible Man goes around the building and read the adventures of the team, and we get to see them in flashbacks. Meanwhile, the Super-Skrull returns yet again to exact his vengeance upon the team. It looks like the Impossible Man, Lockjaw and the Human Torch must team-up to stop the Super-Skrull before whatever sinister means the monster has in store.

Note 1: This is one of two episodes of the second season that has an original script instead of an adaptation. The other being "Nightmare in Green".

Note 2: This entire episode is displayed in a flashback format. Meaning, this is a clip show of recycled short videos from previous episodes.

Note 3: This episode also interweaves with another episode. This episode is titled "The Sentry Sinister", which shows what happened to the other three while they were away.
name: Hopelessly Impossible

deck: Invisible Woman, the Thing and Mr. Fantastic go on a vacay.
description:
The Invisible Woman insists the Fantastic Four to go on a vacation so that they may be refreshed for their next missions. Mr. Fantastic and the Thing agreed to join in with her, but the Human Torch decides to stay behind and take care of the Four Freedoms Plaza. They head to an island to enjoy their trip, but their hopes are soon lowered when they realized the island is the hideout of an active Kree sentry. The Thing, Mr. Fantastic and Invisible Woman must stop the machine before it destroys everything in it's path. Meanwhile at the sealed Attilan, Black Bolt has discovered a way to destroy the force field that was sealed by Maximus after his hostile takeover and the battle between the Inhumans and the Fantastic Four. The way out seems to be easy, but the option may be life threatening for the Inhumans than he thought. Will Black Bolt risk the safety of Attilan's citizens? Will the Fantastic Four destroy the sentry, or perish?

Note 1: This episode is a direct adaptation of Fantastic Four Issue #64.

Note 2: This episode also interweaves with another episode. This episode is titled "Hopelessly Imposible", which shows what happened to the Human Torch while the others were away.
name: The Sentry Sinister

description: The mirakuru sends Roy into an uncontrollable rage and he unleashes on the city. After Roy’s deadly fight with a police officer, Oliver realizes the mirakuru has taken over Roy completely and must figure out a way to stop him. Things get more complicated after Sara declares that Roy is too far gone and the only way to stop him is to kill him. Meanwhile, Thea believes she can breakthrough to Roy so she goes on camera at Moira’s campaign rally to lure him to Verdant. Her ploy works but after Roy attacks Thea, Team Arrow unleashes on him.
name: Seeing Red

deck: Scott and Lydia join forces. Meanwhile, Stilinski faces a review board.
name: De-Void

deck: Doctor Doom's back, for the last time!
description:
Doctor Doom makes a massive return in this episode. While Silver Surfer was wondering the Earth, Doctor Doom and his colleague, with his Doombots trapped him and once again stole the Power Cosmic. Now Doctor Doom has enough power to rule the Earth, but instead of using his power now, he waits for the United Nations to surrender their countries to him, or he'll destroy them. Without any other options left, the United Nations call upon the Fantastic Four to stop Doctor Doom before he finally conquers Earth! But with nearly every superhero in the United States of America entirely pinned down, can the team stop him?

Note 1: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic Four Issues #57 until #60.

Note 2: This episode marks the series's cancellation.

Note 3: Several character in this episode, mainly the Avengers (Iron Man, Vision, She-Hulk, Hercules and Captain America), the New Warriors (Speedball, Darkhawk and Justice), the Marvel Bullpen (identities unspecified), Galactus, Frankie Raye, Namorita and Sabra made only physical cameos as either the heroes battling Doctor Doom or the people the Silver Surfer passed by while he wandered around the world.

Note 4: Although this episode is an adaptation and combination of issues from the Fantastic Four books, it is plainly "The Silver Surfer and the Return of Galactus" all over again, though there were slight plot twists.

Note 5: Like the said episode above, it has a vague similarity with Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer's plot too.
name: Doomsday

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 史上最大の敵！“ジョア”出現!! (Shijō Saidai no Teki! "Joa" Shutsugen!!)

Toriko’s awesomely destructive battle with Starjun is interrupted by the arrival of Joie, an unbelievably deadly adversary who has the power to turn good into evil!
name: The Greatest Enemy in History! 'Joie' Appears!!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 驚愕！黒幕“ジョア”の正体!! (Kyōgaku! Kuromaku "Joa" no Shōtai!!)

After the legendary Knocking Master Jiro unmasks the terrifying evil before them, his life is endangered by his affection for Granny Setsuno! Will Toriko arrive in time to save them both!?
name: Shock! The True Identity of the Mastermind, 'Joie'!!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 終わりの始まり！トリコVSジョア!! (Owari no Hajimari! Toriko VS Joa!!)

Toriko and Starjun forge an unlikely alliance to save Komatsu from a deadly adversary, and a riveting flashback reveals the tragic story of Froese the God Chef!
name: The Beginning of the End! Toriko vs. Joie!!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 起死回生の一撃！四天王、究極技!! (Kishikaisei no Ichigeki! Shitennō, Kyūkyoku Waza!!)

Teppei and Jiro go toe-to-toe, the Four Kings fight together to survive their battle with Joie, and the evil masterminds behind NEO reveal their devious plan! d by his affection for Granny Setsuno! Will Toriko arrive in time to save them both!?
name: Resuscitation Strike! The Four Kings' Ultimate Skill!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 届け，小松の叫び！　トリコ覚醒! (Todoke, Komatsu no Sakebi! Toriko Kakusei!!)

When a battered and beaten Toriko releases the monstrous power of his gourmet cells, only his bond with Komatsu can keep the heroic warrior from going on a deadly rampage!
name: Be Heard, Komatsu's Scream! Toriko Revives!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: トリコと小松 新たな旅の出発!! (Toriko to Komatsu, Arata na Tabi no Shuppatsu!!)

Toriko uses the power of all the ingredients he’s ever eaten to defeat the most deadly opponent he’s ever faced! In the aftermath of battle, Toriko and Komatsu venture into the Gourmet World!
name: Toriko and Komatsu Embark on a New Voyage!

name: Return of the Beast: Part 2

deck: Romero delves deeper into the murder of Miss Watson; the battle between the drug families leaves Dylan caught between a rock and a very hard place; Norma refuses to tell Norman the truth about his blackouts.
name: Meltdown

deck: Scott and company race to rescue Lydia from the clutches of evil as the Nogitsune makes a surprise move, resulting in a tragic loss to the group.
name: Insatiable

deck: Struck by disaster and nearly defeated, Scott and Derek call on their friends and allies to make one last stand.
name: The Divine Move

deck: Ward's betrayal and HYDRA's shocking secrets are revealed as Coulson's team goes undercover on a mission that leaves no one unscathed
description: In the last episode before the epic season finale, Ward's betrayal and Hydra's shocking secrets are revealed as Coulson's team goes undercover on a mission that leaves no one unscathed
name: Ragtag

description: OLIVER CONSIDERS HIS OPTIONS AGAINST SLADE — After Slade (Manu Bennett) threatens to take everything Oliver (Stephen Amell) loves away, Oliver decides the fastest way to stop further bloodshed is to surrender to his enemy. Knowing that surrender will surely lead to Oliver’s death, Diggle (David Ramsey) and Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) go to extreme measures to keep Oliver from confronting Slade. Meanwhile, Thea (Willa Holland) considers leaving town, and Laurel (Katie Cassidy) resumes her crusade against Sebastian Blood (guest star Kevin Alejandro). Finally, Slade unleashes his assault on Starling City.
name: City of Blood
